00:02:51.380 --> 00:02:53.630
How has your view
evolved, and where do you

00:02:53.630 --> 00:02:57.870
think the balance
of power is headed?

00:02:57.870 --> 00:03:01.180
NOAM CHOMSKY: Well, the
internet is obviously

00:03:01.180 --> 00:03:03.120
a tremendous research tool.

00:03:03.120 --> 00:03:05.040
We use it all the time.

00:03:05.040 --> 00:03:09.510
I assume by internet, you mean
more generally-- the whole kind

00:03:09.510 --> 00:03:12.870
of IT system that's developed.

00:03:12.870 --> 00:03:19.820
And, it's certainly useful
for activists and organizers.

00:03:19.820 --> 00:03:24.320
Almost all activist
efforts and enterprises

00:03:24.320 --> 00:03:28.080
involve intercommunication
through the internet.

00:03:28.080 --> 00:03:32.020
On the other hand, we don't
have to talk about the fact

00:03:32.020 --> 00:03:35.800
that it's a tremendous
tool for power systems

00:03:35.800 --> 00:03:40.062
to control and dominate
in all sorts of ways.

00:03:40.062 --> 00:03:45.970
I by now, hardly have to
mention the NSA revelations,

00:03:45.970 --> 00:03:49.290
Edward Snowden's revelations.

00:03:49.290 --> 00:03:52.200
Commercial institutions,
like Google, for example,

00:03:52.200 --> 00:03:55.870
use it to undermine
privacy and independence

00:03:55.870 --> 00:03:59.200
in all kinds of ways.

00:03:59.200 --> 00:04:04.770
So the balance of power is where
it always was, and expending.

00:04:04.770 --> 00:04:06.890
Any technology that's
around is going

00:04:06.890 --> 00:04:10.150
to be used by systems
of concentrated power

00:04:10.150 --> 00:04:12.250
to dominate and control.

00:04:12.250 --> 00:04:14.400
And you can't open
a newspaper now

00:04:14.400 --> 00:04:17.339
without new things appearing.

00:04:17.339 --> 00:04:18.740
Take this morning.

00:04:18.740 --> 00:04:21.040
If you happened to look at
this morning's newspaper,

00:04:21.040 --> 00:04:29.340
there was an associated press
report on some revelations

00:04:29.340 --> 00:04:33.770
that they've dug out
recently about efforts

00:04:33.770 --> 00:04:39.520
to develop by the US government
through USAID, US aid, which

00:04:39.520 --> 00:04:42.850
is supposed to be
a aid organization

00:04:42.850 --> 00:04:49.430
to carry forward the intensive
US efforts to undermine

00:04:49.430 --> 00:04:53.250
and overthrow the
government of Cuba.

00:04:53.250 --> 00:04:54.550
Read the report.

00:04:54.550 --> 00:04:58.480
It's interesting for what it
says and what it doesn't say.

00:04:58.480 --> 00:05:03.410
What it says is that the
government through US aid

00:05:03.410 --> 00:05:08.930
has set up-- tried to set
up-- a kind of social media

00:05:08.930 --> 00:05:15.390
inside Cuba that could be
used to organize the crowds

00:05:15.390 --> 00:05:18.780
to protest with the
people, not really knowing

00:05:18.780 --> 00:05:21.410
who they're working
for what they're doing.

00:05:21.410 --> 00:05:24.080
And the original AP
report, most of which

00:05:24.080 --> 00:05:26.960
didn't get printed, at
least from what I saw,

00:05:26.960 --> 00:05:28.750
says that this has
already been used

00:05:28.750 --> 00:05:32.320
in many other places--
Philippines, Ukraine,

00:05:32.320 --> 00:05:37.210
and so on-- to try to organize
anti-government protests,

00:05:37.210 --> 00:05:40.250
which raises quite a few
questions about what's

00:05:40.250 --> 00:05:42.910
going on around the world.

00:05:42.910 --> 00:05:45.540
Well this is one of
the techniques that's

00:05:45.540 --> 00:05:49.580
being used for subversion,
domination, control.

00:05:49.580 --> 00:05:51.530
This is an Obama
program, incidentally.

00:05:51.530 --> 00:05:53.310
Not Bush.

00:05:53.310 --> 00:05:56.460
And what's said is interesting.

00:05:56.460 --> 00:05:58.800
What isn't said is interesting.

00:05:58.800 --> 00:06:02.680
And here, the power
of the internet

00:06:02.680 --> 00:06:04.620
looms in the background.

00:06:04.620 --> 00:06:08.670
You can quickly find out what
isn't said on the internet

00:06:08.670 --> 00:06:10.540
if you look for it.

00:06:10.540 --> 00:06:15.040
What isn't said is that
this program-- of course,

00:06:15.040 --> 00:06:16.450
it's not called subversion.

00:06:16.450 --> 00:06:18.380
It's called bringing
democracy and so on.

00:06:18.380 --> 00:06:22.500
But this program of trying to
subvert the Cuban government

00:06:22.500 --> 00:06:27.260
is part of a longstanding
war that the US

00:06:27.260 --> 00:06:29.890
has been conducting
against Cuba.

00:06:29.890 --> 00:06:30.890
Longstanding.

00:06:30.890 --> 00:06:34.350
You look at the history
of the US and Cuba--

00:06:34.350 --> 00:06:37.240
it starts in the 1820s.

00:06:37.240 --> 00:06:40.040
Cuba was regarded by
the founding fathers

00:06:40.040 --> 00:06:46.330
as the next conquest
that we have to make.

00:06:46.330 --> 00:06:48.540
Cuba was waiting there.

00:06:48.540 --> 00:06:52.890
We had to take it for ourselves
as we expand and become

00:06:52.890 --> 00:06:55.430
the greatest empire
in the world.

00:06:55.430 --> 00:06:57.290
Well we couldn't do it in 1823.

00:06:57.290 --> 00:06:59.870
There was a deterrent--
the British.

00:06:59.870 --> 00:07:01.810
They were too powerful.

00:07:01.810 --> 00:07:04.610
The British were the main
enemy through the 19th most

00:07:04.610 --> 00:07:08.720
of the 19th century
but the big thinkers,

00:07:08.720 --> 00:07:12.250
like John Quincy Adams--
great grand strategist--

00:07:12.250 --> 00:07:19.350
he recognized and said, while
we can acquire Cuba now,

00:07:19.350 --> 00:07:23.180
it will fall into
our hands by the laws

00:07:23.180 --> 00:07:26.430
of political gravitation,
just as an apple

00:07:26.430 --> 00:07:28.170
falls from the tree.

00:07:28.170 --> 00:07:33.080
Meaning, over time, the US
will become more powerful.

00:07:33.080 --> 00:07:37.110
Britain's power will decline,
And we'll be able to take Cuba.

00:07:37.110 --> 00:07:38.880
And in fact, that's
what happened.

00:07:38.880 --> 00:07:44.470
In 1898, Cuba was liberating
itself from Spain,

00:07:44.470 --> 00:07:49.360
and the US intervened in what's
called here Liberation of Cuba,

00:07:49.360 --> 00:07:54.170
but in fact, was the prevention
of the liberation of Cuba

00:07:54.170 --> 00:07:55.660
by Cubans.

00:07:55.660 --> 00:07:58.940
The US took over the
island-- one of several.

00:07:58.940 --> 00:08:02.610
Puerto Rico, Hawaii was
stolen from its inhabitants

00:08:02.610 --> 00:08:07.035
the same year, and Cuba became
a colony-- a virtual colony.

00:08:07.035 --> 00:08:08.530
Well, something
quite interesting

00:08:08.530 --> 00:08:11.330
happened that's
highly relevant today.

00:08:11.330 --> 00:08:12.290
Highly relevant.

00:08:12.290 --> 00:08:15.200
But never mentioned, but you
can find it on the internet

00:08:15.200 --> 00:08:17.360
if you like.

00:08:17.360 --> 00:08:21.140
At gun point, the
US imposed a treaty

00:08:21.140 --> 00:08:24.470
on Cuba, Platt
Ammendment, it's called,

00:08:24.470 --> 00:08:28.470
in which Cuba granted
the United States control

00:08:28.470 --> 00:08:32.490
over eastern Cuba-- so
what we call Guantanamo.

00:08:32.490 --> 00:08:35.659
Happens to include
Cuba's major port-- it's

00:08:35.659 --> 00:08:37.929
only port oriented
towards Europe,

00:08:37.929 --> 00:08:40.409
which is where its
main trade would be.

00:08:40.409 --> 00:08:42.820
Of course, the Cubans
had no voice in this.

00:08:42.820 --> 00:08:45.590
We just took it over.

00:08:45.590 --> 00:08:48.370
And we've had it for 110 years.

00:08:48.370 --> 00:08:51.400
Cuba's been trying to get
it back, but we refuse.

00:08:51.400 --> 00:08:54.570
The purpose has no
strategic interest for us.

00:08:54.570 --> 00:08:57.740
It's used for
storage of refugees,

00:08:57.740 --> 00:09:02.080
like if Haitians flee from
monstrous dictatorships

00:09:02.080 --> 00:09:06.130
that we support in Haiti,
we're supposed to accept them

00:09:06.130 --> 00:09:08.130
under international
law's refugees.

00:09:08.130 --> 00:09:11.320
But instead, you send them
off Cuba-- to Guantanamo--

00:09:11.320 --> 00:09:14.930
as a storage place, of course,
used as a torture chamber.

00:09:14.930 --> 00:09:16.170
The Cubans want it back.

00:09:16.170 --> 00:09:17.470
We won't give it to them.

00:09:17.470 --> 00:09:19.060
Does this remind
you of something

00:09:19.060 --> 00:09:22.568
that's happening in
world affairs right now?

00:09:22.568 --> 00:09:25.430
Yeah.

00:09:25.430 --> 00:09:27.080
Russia took over Crimea.

00:09:30.250 --> 00:09:35.292
Just as we've taken over eastern
Cuba for 110 years at gun

00:09:35.292 --> 00:09:37.510
point.

00:09:37.510 --> 00:09:41.070
We don't formally annex
it, but we dominate it.

00:09:41.070 --> 00:09:45.790
Russia has a much stronger case
than the United States does.

00:09:45.790 --> 00:09:48.130
Crimea is primarily Russian.

00:09:48.130 --> 00:09:52.660
Its population overwhelmingly
supports Russia.

00:09:52.660 --> 00:09:54.920
It's got major
strategic significance.

00:09:54.920 --> 00:09:57.460
It's Russia's only
warm water port.

00:09:57.460 --> 00:10:01.190
It's the base for their fleet.

00:10:01.190 --> 00:10:02.840
It's right on the
border of Russia.

00:10:02.840 --> 00:10:07.830
Russia's surrounded by hostile
military alliance-- NATO.

00:10:07.830 --> 00:10:11.320
And for them, it's of great
strategic significance.

00:10:11.320 --> 00:10:14.030
Cuba for us is nothing.

00:10:14.030 --> 00:10:14.740
Guantanamo.

00:10:14.740 --> 00:10:17.370
It's just a means of
trying to undermine

00:10:17.370 --> 00:10:20.340
Cuba-- prevent
Cuban development.

00:10:20.340 --> 00:10:22.100
And the United
States, of course,

00:10:22.100 --> 00:10:25.920
has been at war with
Cuba since 1959,

00:10:25.920 --> 00:10:29.230
when Cuba finally
did liberate itself.

00:10:29.230 --> 00:10:34.060
Immediately, the US began an
attack on Cuba under Kennedy.

00:10:34.060 --> 00:10:37.360
A massive terrorist
operation was

00:10:37.360 --> 00:10:41.650
organized "to bring the
terrors of the earth to Cuba,"

00:10:41.650 --> 00:10:44.560
was Arthur Schlesinger's
phrase describing it

00:10:44.560 --> 00:10:47.110
in his biography of
Robert Kennedy, who

00:10:47.110 --> 00:10:48.460
was in charge of it.

00:10:48.460 --> 00:10:50.760
It almost destroyed the world.

00:10:50.760 --> 00:10:54.150
It was a major factor that
led to the missile crisis.

00:10:54.150 --> 00:10:55.540
And it's gone on.

00:10:55.540 --> 00:10:58.582
It went on afterwards.

00:10:58.582 --> 00:11:03.770
The terror based in Florida has
gone on almost without a stop.

00:11:03.770 --> 00:11:06.460
On top of that, there's
an economic embargo

00:11:06.460 --> 00:11:10.390
to strangle the country,
opposed by the entire world.

00:11:10.390 --> 00:11:13.600
Take a look at the votes--
annual votes in the General

00:11:13.600 --> 00:11:16.800
Assembly, which don't
get reported here.

00:11:16.800 --> 00:11:20.480
It's 180 to two-- US
and Israel sometimes.

00:11:20.480 --> 00:11:23.040
The Marshall Islands
or something.

00:11:23.040 --> 00:11:27.390
Well, all of this is part of
the background to the AP story

00:11:27.390 --> 00:11:31.110
about today's effort to
subvert the government of Cuba.

00:11:31.110 --> 00:11:34.080
Well, coming back to the
internet, what's interesting

00:11:34.080 --> 00:11:39.000
is what is available, and
what isn't readily available,

00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:40.760
because people don't see it.

00:11:40.760 --> 00:11:42.930
Like, you won't find
a word about anything

00:11:42.930 --> 00:11:47.680
I said in the press, or in
commentary, or discussion,

00:11:47.680 --> 00:11:49.960
although it's all
extremely timely.

00:11:49.960 --> 00:11:51.560
Very timely.

00:11:51.560 --> 00:11:54.080
Not arcane scholarship.

00:11:54.080 --> 00:11:57.740
But it's right in front of
our eyes, but not there.

00:11:57.740 --> 00:12:00.130
And when you come back to
the power of the internet,

00:12:00.130 --> 00:12:02.710
I think it comes back to us.

00:12:02.710 --> 00:12:04.370
We don't use it.

00:12:04.370 --> 00:12:09.240
We don't use the resource for
the purposes for which it could

00:12:09.240 --> 00:12:13.720
be used-- to break through
the silence, oppression,

00:12:13.720 --> 00:12:17.520
domination, terror,
violence, and bring

00:12:17.520 --> 00:12:19.690
the reality of the
world to people.

00:12:19.690 --> 00:12:22.580
So the internet, potentially,
is a wonderful tool,

00:12:22.580 --> 00:12:25.320
but only if you
decide to use it.

00:12:25.320 --> 00:12:31.160
If you decide to leave it in
the hands of private power,

00:12:31.160 --> 00:12:34.060
of power systems whether
state or private,

00:12:34.060 --> 00:12:36.630
sure-- it'll be used as a
way to oppress, undermine

00:12:36.630 --> 00:12:37.940
and dominate.

00:12:37.940 --> 00:12:39.090
But that's a choice.

00:12:39.090 --> 00:12:40.610
Don't have to.

