And the communication
is very restricted.

00:57:42.710 --> 00:57:46.470
A simple formula is
things like that.

00:57:46.470 --> 00:57:51.070
So does it have a
dumbing down effect?

00:57:51.070 --> 00:57:53.050
I kind of doubt it, frankly.

00:57:53.050 --> 00:57:56.340
But, you know, it is a
topic that could be studied.

00:57:56.340 --> 00:57:58.130
It is being studied, in fact.

00:57:58.130 --> 00:58:01.920
But as far as I know,
there are no real results,

00:58:01.920 --> 00:58:03.950
and I think it
would be surprising,

00:58:03.950 --> 00:58:07.470
because it's all
kind of superficial.

00:58:07.470 --> 00:58:09.830
It does add a kind
of superficiality

00:58:09.830 --> 00:58:13.920
to life, which may
not be a good thing.

00:58:13.920 --> 00:58:16.660
I think it's probably
harmful in the long run.

00:58:16.660 --> 00:58:22.950
But to try to-- I feel like I'm
bringing coals to Newcastle.

00:58:22.950 --> 00:58:24.540
You people know a
lot more about this

00:58:24.540 --> 00:58:28.030
than I do, because I don't
use any of this stuff,

00:58:28.030 --> 00:58:31.366
except with my grandchildren,
when I have to.

00:58:31.366 --> 00:58:32.490
Is there one last question?

00:58:32.490 --> 00:58:35.070
We have time for
a quick question.

00:58:35.070 --> 00:58:35.570
There.

00:58:39.400 --> 00:58:43.640
Is the-- so the diversity
of languages and cultures

00:58:43.640 --> 00:58:46.630
is wonderful, but if there is
on the other side, if you would

00:58:46.630 --> 00:58:49.330
say anything, if you
would, sort of allow

00:58:49.330 --> 00:58:55.110
that having a unified
language and common culture

00:58:55.110 --> 00:59:00.110
helps communication and
may advance world peace?

00:59:00.110 --> 00:59:02.340
Well I don't if
it advances peace.

00:59:02.340 --> 00:59:05.300
In fact, it seems to have
the opposite, because you're

00:59:05.300 --> 00:59:10.540
forcing people into
situations of conflict.

00:59:10.540 --> 00:59:13.310
And the one language
that dominates

00:59:13.310 --> 00:59:16.030
is just the most powerful
state in the world.

00:59:16.030 --> 00:59:17.740
But there's an advantage,
to having, say,

00:59:17.740 --> 00:59:20.130
a single language for science.

00:59:20.130 --> 00:59:24.940
OK, so by now, English is pretty
much the language of science.

00:59:24.940 --> 00:59:28.590
When I got to MIT
60 years ago, I

00:59:28.590 --> 00:59:33.570
was teaching scientific French
and scientific German-- all

00:59:33.570 --> 00:59:36.690
graduate students
in every field had

00:59:36.690 --> 00:59:39.950
to pass an exam in
French and German.

00:59:39.950 --> 00:59:44.010
It was a complete fake,
but that was kind of

00:59:44.010 --> 00:59:47.280
like a residue of the
pre-second World War period.

00:59:47.280 --> 00:59:48.890
But it was true.

00:59:48.890 --> 00:59:52.840
You go back 70 years,
a civil engineer

00:59:52.840 --> 00:59:54.630
had to know French or German.

00:59:54.630 --> 00:59:57.930
OK now, that's all gone.

00:59:57.930 --> 01:00:00.625
All around most of the world,
the language of science

01:00:00.625 --> 01:00:01.760
is English.

01:00:01.760 --> 01:00:03.310
That's helpful.

01:00:03.310 --> 01:00:05.110
On the other hand,
exactly as you say,

01:00:05.110 --> 01:00:11.380
there's also-- if that
extend from just some mode

01:00:11.380 --> 01:00:15.390
of communication to the
actual languages of life,

01:00:15.390 --> 01:00:17.530
it would be a real loss.

01:00:17.530 --> 01:00:19.860
We would lose cultural wealth.

01:00:19.860 --> 01:00:22.085
Actually, if you live
in the United States,

01:00:22.085 --> 01:00:25.880
and you travel abroad,
you see it very quickly.

01:00:25.880 --> 01:00:30.020
The United States is an
extremely insular society.

01:00:30.020 --> 01:00:33.570
People don't know anything
about the outside world.

01:00:33.570 --> 01:00:39.110
Students in colleges don't
know where France is.

01:00:39.110 --> 01:00:41.310
It's just-- they
don't know anything.

01:00:41.310 --> 01:00:45.070
It's remarkably different from
Europe and other countries.

01:00:45.070 --> 01:00:47.470
And part of the
reason is that, you

01:00:47.470 --> 01:00:50.710
can go 3,000 miles
in the United States,

01:00:50.710 --> 01:00:54.360
and it looks exactly
like where you came from.

01:00:54.360 --> 01:00:57.960
Go to Boston to Los Angeles, the
weather's a little different,

01:00:57.960 --> 01:00:59.800
but everything else is the same.

01:00:59.800 --> 01:01:01.760
The accent is
slightly different.

01:01:01.760 --> 01:01:05.490
You go 100 miles in Europe, and
you're in a different society.

01:01:05.490 --> 01:01:07.740
So you just kind
of automatically

01:01:07.740 --> 01:01:13.200
gain comprehension of the
richness and complexity of life

01:01:13.200 --> 01:01:16.690
that's missing when
societies are homogeneous.

01:01:16.690 --> 01:01:20.110
Of course American society
isn't literally homogeneous.

01:01:20.110 --> 01:01:23.290
But, comparatively
speaking, it is.

01:01:23.290 --> 01:01:25.700
And I think that's
the kind of loss

01:01:25.700 --> 01:01:29.490
you would get if,
in fact, you moved

01:01:29.490 --> 01:01:32.830
towards a universal language.

01:01:32.830 --> 01:01:36.410
Also, I just don't think
there's any possibility that's

01:01:36.410 --> 01:01:36.960
happening.

01:01:36.960 --> 01:01:38.960
As I said, in
Europe, there's now

01:01:38.960 --> 01:01:43.810
actually a reaction against
the unifying tendencies

01:01:43.810 --> 01:01:45.830
of the European Union--
more regionalization,

01:01:45.830 --> 01:01:48.390
regional languages, cultures.

01:01:48.390 --> 01:01:50.020
It's not just
languages, incidentally.

01:01:50.020 --> 01:01:53.060
So take Catalonia,
which I mentioned.

01:01:53.060 --> 01:01:58.280
Under the Franco dictatorship,
Catalonian language and culture

01:01:58.280 --> 01:02:00.420
were totally suppressed.

01:02:00.420 --> 01:02:03.660
They could not be
exhibited in public.

01:02:03.660 --> 01:02:07.860
But, if you go to
Barcelona today,

01:02:07.860 --> 01:02:11.590
let's say, you can
on Sunday morning,

01:02:11.590 --> 01:02:15.500
if you're downtown in Barcelona,
take a look at the cathedral.

01:02:15.500 --> 01:02:21.500
There's people swarming towards
the cathedral-- folk singers,

01:02:21.500 --> 01:02:25.610
folk dances, Catalan
cultures being revived.

01:02:25.610 --> 01:02:28.130
It's a rich culture
being revived.

01:02:28.130 --> 01:02:29.950
It was kind of
there, underground.

01:02:29.950 --> 01:02:31.480
Now it's open.

01:02:31.480 --> 01:02:34.960
And I think that's
just healthy for life.

01:02:34.960 --> 01:02:41.167
[APPLAUSE]

